| Type of CSS | Location              | Use Case                         |
| ----------- | --------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Inline      | Inside HTML element   | Quick styling, single element    |
| Internal    | `<style>` in `<head>` | Page-specific styles             |
| External    | Separate `.css` file  | Reusable, clean, multi-page site |


!important Rule
The !important rule is used to override all other conflicting rules, including inline styles.

p {
  color: green !important;
}


## CSS Syntax: 
selector {
  property: value;
}
Example:

h1 {
  color: purple;
  font-size: 24px;

h1 → Selector (the HTML element)
color → Property (what you want to change)
purple → Value (how you want it to appear)
